stylometry: Bayes Therom uses past data to predict how future data will behave. This is important because businesses can use this to predict how their customers will behave in the future. The business can then alter their product, company structure, or marketing to better suit their customers. Bayes Therom allows you to attempt to predict how to best run your business in the future. Posterior probabilities are determined by taking past data and dividing it by the current data. We need the posterior probabilities because they are used as an assumption of new probabilities. An example would be if a customer typically buys cookies 35% of the time they go to the grocery store we can assume that they will continue this pattern and the cookie company can expect this level of demand.
